for  <span class="math">A = \\alpha(0) - \\omega(0)</span>  ;  <span class="math">S = p_S \\lambda - p_T \\lambda</span> . (5)</p>

    <h4 id="sec-22" class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6"><strong>Lemma 13.</strong> <em>Equation 5 implies</em></h4>

    <p class="text-gray-300"><span class="math">$\\omega_{2d} = \\frac{p_S \\lambda - p_T \\lambda}{p_S \\lambda - p_T \\lambda e^{-(p_S \\lambda - p_T \\lambda)2d}}.</span>$</p>

    <p class="text-gray-300">By the definition of <em>ω</em>2<em>d</em>, it is precisely the fraction of <em>u</em>'s blocks that have no conflicting blocks created by <em>v</em>. The blocks which contribute to the growth of the main chain are can thus be counted by considering all of <em>v</em>'s blocks as valid, and adding to those all of <em>u</em>'s non-conflicting blocks. Altogether, we obtain</p>

    <p class="text-gray-300"><span class="math">$\\beta(\\lambda) = p_T \\lambda + \\omega_{2d} \\cdot p_S \\lambda =</span>$</p>

